reviews.reviewText: ASSEMBLY INSTRUCTIONS ARE A LITTLE LACKING, BUT THATS NORMAL WITH ANYTHING ASSEMBLED. VERY NICE PANTRY. EVERYTHING ALLIGNED PERFECTLY. MATERIAL SEEMS WELL CONSTRUCTED.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I am a 61 year young woman of not too good of health and I put this together myself. I paced myself so it took me about 4 hours, but I was careful to be prepared by laying everything out and grabbing my rubber mallot and electric screwdriver (I have a nice blister on my hand from hand screwing the screws in so use gloves). The instructions say not to use an electric screwdriver but I did it carefully anyway, with no problems. If you go slow and concentrate, you should have no problems. The doors even lined up perfectly upon completion. Note: have some Elmer's or wood glue handy for the dowels. Grab a rubber mallot. Don't use the wall anchors unless you are in an earthquake zone, and then you will have to drill holes for them as there are no predrilled holes for the wall brackets/anchors. I wish it was taller, but it is still a nice cabinet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Took a risk, but am happy with this buy!
reviews.reviewText: There weren’t many reviews for this product when I bought it, but so far I’m enjoying it!! Looks nice in my kitchen and is small enough to add space without being in the way. If I had room, I’d probably buy another one!! I’m probably overloading the shelves. I think the limit was only 11lbs per shelf. We’ll see! One day I’ll get it organized but it’s doing a great job hiding my pantry items for now.
